---

# SclJet SQL ORDER BY expressions

An `ORDER BY` key may be any scalar expression, not just a column: `ORDER BY salary * -1`,
`ORDER BY UPPER(name)`, `ORDER BY LENGTH(name), name`, and `ORDER BY salary * 2 DESC LIMIT 3`. Keys
still compose (multi-key, per-key ASC/DESC) and the sort is stable. Every result is byte-identical to
reference sqlite3 running the same SQL on the same file (verified out-of-band); locked across backends.

[ByteSlice, SqliteValue, SqlInteger, SqlText, buildTableDatabase](std/scljet/index.ssc)
[queryImage, renderRows](std/scljet/sql.ssc)

```scalascript
def show(db: ByteSlice, sql: String): Unit =
  queryImage(db, sql) match
    case Left(m) => println(sql + " => ERR:" + m)
    case Right(rows) => println(sql + " => " + renderRows(rows).toString)

buildTableDatabase(512, 1, 1, "emp", "CREATE TABLE emp(id INTEGER, name TEXT, salary INTEGER, dept INTEGER)",
  List(List(SqlInteger(1L), SqlText("ann"), SqlInteger(100L), SqlInteger(10L)),
       List(SqlInteger(2L), SqlText("Bob"), SqlInteger(250L), SqlInteger(20L)),
       List(SqlInteger(3L), SqlText("charlie"), SqlInteger(300L), SqlInteger(10L)),
       List(SqlInteger(4L), SqlText("dan"), SqlInteger(150L), SqlInteger(30L)),
       List(SqlInteger(5L), SqlText("ed"), SqlInteger(250L), SqlInteger(20L)))) match
  case Left(error) => println("build-error:" + error.message)
  case Right(db) =>
    show(db, "SELECT id FROM emp ORDER BY salary * -1")
    show(db, "SELECT name FROM emp ORDER BY UPPER(name)")
    show(db, "SELECT id FROM emp ORDER BY dept, salary DESC")
    show(db, "SELECT id, salary FROM emp ORDER BY salary * 2 DESC LIMIT 3")
    show(db, "SELECT name FROM emp ORDER BY LENGTH(name), name")
```
